MEP | REQUIREMENTS FINAL

ATLAS CONSTRUCTION PROJECT
Mechanical, Electrical, Plumbing Design Specification
Version: FINAL | Date: 2026-03-03 | Classification: INTERNAL

====================================================================
MECHANICAL SYSTEMS
====================================================================

1.1 HVAC GENERAL REQUIREMENTS
- Design Standard: AS 1228 (Commercial building standards)
- Thermal Comfort: ASHRAE 55-2023
- Air Change Rates: 8 ACH minimum, 12 ACH office areas
- Humidity Control: 30-60% RH in occupied spaces
- System Type: Central Chilled Water + Central Heating

1.2 COOLING SYSTEM
- Cooling Load: 4,500 kW (peak)
- Chiller Configuration: 2 x 2,250 kW (N+1 redundancy)
- Chiller Type: Centrifugal, hermetic
- Capacity Modulation: 25-100% via inlet guide vanes
- Refrigerant: HFC-134a (zero ODP)

1.3 HEATING SYSTEM
- Heating Load: 2,200 kW (peak)
- Boiler Configuration: 2 x 1,100 kW (N+1 redundancy)
- Boiler Type: Large cube water-tube gas-fired
- Efficiency: ≥ 94% (seasonal)
- Fuel: Mains Natural Gas

1.4 VENTILATION
- Outdoor Air: 8-15 L/s per person (variable per zone)
- Exhaust Systems: 100% make-up air balance
- Filters: MERV-13 minimum (prefilters)
- Ductwork: Galvanized steel, sealed, insulated
- Noise Level: ≤ 35 dB(A) in occupied spaces

1.5 DUCTWORK DESIGN
- Main Supply Duct: 800-1000mm diameter
- Return Duct: 900-1200mm diameter
- Exhaust Duct: 600-800mm diameter
- Velocity: 5-6 m/s maximum (noise consideration)
- Insulation: 50mm polyurethane foam, R-2.0

====================================================================
ELECTRICAL SYSTEMS
====================================================================

2.1 ELECTRICAL SUPPLY
- Supply Voltage: 400V, 3-phase, 50Hz (Australian standard)
- Incoming Supply Capacity: 2000A main switchboard
- Backup Power: 1500 kW diesel generator (48-hour runtime)
- UPS System: 500 kW for critical loads (≥ 15 minutes autonomy)

2.2 DISTRIBUTION SYSTEM
- Main Distribution Boards: 400A x 13 (one per floor)
- Lighting Load: 15 W/m² (LED throughout)
- Power Load: 50 W/m² (office areas)
- Circuits: Max 20A for general purpose, 16A for lighting
- Earthing: TN-S system with RCDs (AS/NZS 3000)

2.3 LIGHTING DESIGN
- Illuminance: 500 lux (office), 300 lux (corridors)
- Type: LED luminaires (≥ 90 CRI, 4000K CCT)
- Control: Occupancy sensors + manual override in all zones
- Dimming: 0-100% via DALI control system
- Energy Efficiency: ≥ 91 lumens per watt

2.4 EMERGENCY SYSTEMS
- Emergency Lighting: Backup battery + LED (3-hour duration)
- Exit Signage: LED, maintained + non-maintained types
- Fire Alarm: Category A system, fully automatic (AS 1670)
- Smoke Detection: Photoelectric types throughout
- Manual Call Points: Every 30m corridor length

2.5 COMMUNICATIONS INFRASTRUCTURE
- Data Cabling: Category 6A (all work areas)
- WiFi Coverage: 802.11ax (WiFi 6) mesh network
- Telephone System: IP-PBX, 200 extensions
- Structured Cabling: Compliant AS/NZS 3080.2
- Fiber Optic: Multi-mode backbone (MMF) 12F

====================================================================
PLUMBING SYSTEMS
====================================================================

3.1 WATER SUPPLY
- Main Inlet: 50mm diameter, single entry point
- Water Pressure: 200-400 kPa (regulated)
- Pressure Tank: 5,000L capacity
- Backup Pump: Submersible, 25 L/s capacity
- Water Quality: Potable grade per AS 4020

3.2 DISTRIBUTION (Hot & Cold)
- Cold Water: Copper or HDPE piping
- Hot Water: Copper or HDPE with heating elements
- Insulation: 50mm polyurethane foam on hot water
- Pipe Sizing: AS 3500.1 (minimum velocity 0.6-2.0 m/s)
- Temperature: 50-60°C hot water (thermostat controlled)

3.3 FIXTURES & FITTINGS
- Toilet Seats: Dual-flush (3/6L), pressure-assisted
- Faucets: Sensor-activated (non-contact) in public areas
- Showers: Thermostatic cartridges (safety limit 50°C)
- Urinals: Dual-flush waterless options (50% reduction)

3.4 WASTE WATER
- Drainage System: Gravity + pump discharge
- Sump Pit: 10 m³ capacity (basement collection)
- Drainage Pump: 50 L/s @ 50m TDH (N+1 backup)
- Grease Trap: Required for kitchen areas
- Treatment: Septic system for gray water recycling

3.5 FIRE PROTECTION (Water)
- System Type: Wet sprinkler system (AS 1851)
- Coverage: 100% of building except stairwells
- Sprinkler Heads: Pendent, 4.5mm orifice
- Pressure: 400-600 kPa at sprinkler heads
- Response Time: ≤ 60 seconds
- Water Storage: 500,000L dedicated fire tanks

====================================================================
COORDINATION REQUIREMENTS
====================================================================

4.1 ARCHITECTURAL INTERFACE
- Ductwork to clear ceiling height (min 2.5m occupied)
- Piping routing via coordinated core zones
- Equipment rooms: 20m2 per floor (HVAC + electrical)
- Access requirements: 1.2m minimum service clearance

4.2 STRUCTURAL INTERFACE
- All heavy equipment supported independently
- Vibration isolation: Springs + neoprene pads
- Pipe hangers: Every 2m vertical, 3m horizontal runs
- Bolt penetrations: Sleeved through concrete elements

